objects.description: TRINITY malware used by {{LinkById|G0037}} identifies payment card track data on the victim and then copies it to a local file in a subdirectory of C:\Windows\. Once the malware collects the data, {{LinkById|G0037}} actors compressed data and moved it to another staging system before exfiltration.

external_references.description: FireEye Threat Intelligence. (2016, April). Follow the Money: Dissecting the Operations of the Cyber Crime Group FIN6. Retrieved June 1, 2016.
